The paper deals with the problem of populating ontology graphs, which is a core problem in the Semantic Web community. The proposed method, On2Vec, is a graph embedding method that uses translation-based models to encode comprehensive semantic relations in ontology graphs. This involves encoding concepts and relations into low-dimensional embedding spaces while preserving relational properties, as well as performing focused learning of hierarchical relation facts. 

Given this, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, which deals with artificial intelligence and machine learning methods for solving complex problems. The paper also involves graph embedding, which is a common topic in the sub-category cs.LG (machine learning). The use of ontology graphs and the focus on comprehensive semantic relations suggest that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DB (databases), cs.IR (information retrieval), and cs.CL (computational linguistics).
